doctors.does_not_accept_new_patients_message_htm: Dr Hunter Tuon does not take on new patients online. Please call the practice to book an appointment.
doctors.statement: Hunter graduated from the University of Sydney in Medicine in 1999. He worked and trained in Canberra.Hospital prior to 2002 in areas of general practice and general surgery as well as pediatrics. He undertook general practice training from 2003 and became a fellow of the Royal Australian College of General Practitioners in 2005. His interests include preventive health, Implanon insertion and travel medicine.

doctors.does_not_accept_new_patients_message_htm: Dr Heather Whitson does not take on new patients online. Please call the practice to book an appointment.
doctors.statement:
Please note Dr Whitson is not able to see any new patients at this time. Please only book in with Dr Whitson if you have seen her before. 
Heather is a graduate of the University of New South Wales. She has completed two post-graduate diplomas – one in Obstetrics & Gynaecology, and one in Palliative Medicine – in addition to completing a certificate course in Sexual & Reproductive Health from Family Planning Australia. She is a fellow of the Royal Australian College of General Practitioners. Heather has worked in many rural and remote areas of Australia in general practice, Aboriginal health and palliative care. She has worked in the United Kingdom in the areas of psychiatry and emergency medicine. She enjoys all areas of general practice but has special interest in women’s health, travel medicine and palliative care. In addition to working at Montrose, Heather teaches in the School of Medicine at the University of Notre Dame Australia.

doctors.does_not_accept_new_patients_message_htm: Dr Rebecca Chan does not take on new patients online. Please call the practice to book an appointment.
doctors.statement:
Rebecca graduated from the University of Notre Dame Sydney in 2012 and has since worked in a number of hospitals and general practices throughout Sydney.  She has completed both the Diploma of Child Health and the Family Planning national certificate in sexual and reproductive health.  In addition, she holds a Graduate Diploma in Genetic Counseling from the University of Melbourne.  She has special interests in paediatrics and women's health, and is accredited to provide implanon and IUD insertion and antenatal shared care.  Outside of work, she is kept busy with her two young boys and enjoys running and good food.
Please note Rebecca will be on maternity  leave from the 19th of March. She will return the to practice in August 2021.

doctors.does_not_accept_new_patients_message_htm: Dr Dileni Fernando does not take on new patients online. Please call the practice to book an appointment.
doctors.statement:
Please be aware that Dr Dileni Fernando is unable to take on any new patients as this time. If you have not seen Dileni before please call reception on 9660 6788 to discuss alternative practitioners.
Dileni is a graduate of the University of Newcastle. She has completed the certificate course in Sexual Health and Reproductive Medicine from Family Planning Australia and is a Fellow of the Royal Australian College of General Practitioners. She is accredited to provide antenatal shared care at Royal Prince Alfred Hospital and the Royal Hospital for Women. She has worked in a variety of hospitals and general practices  across NSW in addition to working for several years in a sexual health clinic. She enjoys the diversity and holistic nature of general practice and has special interests in sexual health, men's and women's health, preventative health and travel medicine.

doctors.does_not_accept_new_patients_message_htm: Dr Catherine Choi does not take on new patients online. Please call the practice to book an appointment.
doctors.statement: Catherine completed her medical degree at The University of Sydney, and subsequently gained experience at various tertiary hospitals and general practices across NSW. She has completed additional professional education in the form of a Diploma of Child Health, Certificate in Reproductive & Sexual Health and Certificate in Skin Cancer Medicine. She is also registered to provide antenatal care with Royal Prince Alfred Hospital, Royal North Shore Hospital and the Royal Hospital for Women. Additionally, Catherine is qualified to provide basic focussed psychological strategies to support mental health. She is also qualified for Implanon insertions. Catherine has a love for the breadth of general practice, is committed to constant learning and is passionate about providing high-quality, personalised care to people from all walks of life. This includes women’s health, sexual health and antental care, men’s health, mental health and promoting healthy lifestyle changes. Outside of work, Catherine loves travelling to experience new cultures, attempting barre/pump classes and eating her herb garden much faster than it grows.

doctors.does_not_accept_new_patients_message_htm: Declan O'Connor does not take on new patients online. Please call the practice to book an appointment.
doctors.statement:
Declan has worked in private practice since graduating from the University of Newcastle, working in multiple clinics on the North Shore and in the Eastern Suburbs. He jointly runs and manages podiatry practicesin the North Shore area and the city where his focus is on promoting foot health and improving body posture as well as providing domiciliary podiatry care to patients across Sydney in their homes, and in retirement villages & aged care facilities.
Declan enjoys diabetic foot care, neurological & vascular testing, and using orthoses to treat musculoskeletal aches & pains and to improve posture, and nail surgery, but is available for any foot or lower limb issue big or small. Declan is available every Tuesday from 8am and alternate Saturday’s to continue the excellent podiatry care that Ed Pickersgill was providing.

doctors.does_not_accept_new_patients_message_htm: Daniella Thrassis does not take on new patients online. Please call the practice to book an appointment.
doctors.statement:
Daniella graduated from the University of Sydney in 2010 and went on to complete a double masters degree in Sports and Musculoskeletal Physiotherapy from Griffith University in 2016. As a result she is an APA titled Sports and Musculoskeletal physiotherapist and currently is the Rehabilitation Physiotherapist at NSW Waratahs. Previously she has worked in large multidisciplinary sports medicine practice, Sydney Roosters NRL and Sydney University Rugby Club. She is also a Clinical Pilates instructor. As a result she has seen and rehabilitated a variety of conditions and injuries from both the sporting and general population.

Combining her clinical and treatment skills with her pilates and rehabilitation experience Danni is passionate about using her manual skills, rehabilitation abilities and understanding of complex musculoskeletal injuries to help her patients. She believes that this will help them to achieve their goals of returning to sport, or activity, pain free.

doctors.does_not_accept_new_patients_message_htm: Shane Kertanegara does not take on new patients online. Please call the practice to book an appointment.
doctors.statement: Shane Kertanegara graduated from the University of Sydney in 2006 with 1st class honours and the University Medal. He is the current Head Physiotherapist at the NSW Waratahs and has been at the club for 10 years. A published author and current lecturer at the University of Sydney, Shane’s previous roles include Head Physiotherapist of Australian U20s Junior Wallabies and Sydney University Rugby Club. Shane has an interest in treating lower limb injuries, hip and groin pain, tendinopathies and the shoulder joint. He will aim to establish an accurate diagnosis, clear management plan and use effective treatment options to guide you through your condition.

doctors.does_not_accept_new_patients_message_htm: Dr Ramanan (Rams) Chandrabalan does not take on new patients online. Please call the practice to book an appointment.
doctors.statement:
Rams completed his medical degree at the University of Sydney and completed his internship and
residency at Concord, Canterbury & Broken Hill Hospitals. Prior to his career in medicine, Rams was
an optometrist having completing his optometry degree at the University of New South Wales.
Rams enjoys the variety of general practice and enjoys looking after families, young and old! He has
particular interests in chronic disease management, sexual health, men’s health, women’s health
and paediatrics, having completed the Diploma in Child Health in 2016. Rams is an antenatal shared
care provider with RPA & Canterbury Hospitals and is certified to insert and remove Implanon
contraception. Furthermore, Rams is also an accredited S100 Hepatitis B & HIV (including PrEP &
PEP) medication prescriber. In addition to his clinical practice, Rams frequently supervises medical
students and trainee doctors, and is an examiner for the Royal Australian College of General
Practitioners.
Outside of work Rams enjoys spending time with friends and family and being comprehensively
beaten at tennis on a regular basis.
doctors.statement_html: Rams completed his medical degree at the University of Sydney and completed his internship and residency at Concord, Canterbury & Broken Hill Hospitals. Prior to his career in medicine, Rams was an optometrist having completing his optometry degree at the University of New South Wales. Rams enjoys the variety of general practice and enjoys looking after families, young and old! He has particular interests in chronic disease management, sexual health, men’s health, women’s health and paediatrics, having completed the Diploma in Child Health in 2016. Rams is an antenatal shared care provider with RPA & Canterbury Hospitals and is certified to insert and remove Implanon contraception. Furthermore, Rams is also an accredited S100 Hepatitis B & HIV (including PrEP & PEP) medication prescriber. In addition to his clinical practice, Rams frequently supervises medical students and trainee doctors, and is an examiner for the Royal Australian College of General Practitioners. Outside of work Rams enjoys spending time with friends and family and being comprehensively beaten at tennis on a regular basis.

doctors.does_not_accept_new_patients_message_htm: Dr Covid 19 Vaccinator does not take on new patients online. Please call the practice to book an appointment.
Dr Frances Chen does not take on new patients online. Please call the practice to book an appointment.
doctors.statement: Frances graduated from the University of New South Wales with a Bachelor of Medical Studies and Doctor of Medicine with Distinction. She has trained in a number of Sydney hospitals including Concord Hospital, Royal North Shore Hospital and Mona Vale Hospital before entering General Practice.  Frances enjoys all aspects of General Practice. She has additional qualifications and training in paediatrics, women's health and sexual health through the Diploma of Child Health, Certificate for Women's Health and National Certificate in Reproductive and Sexual Health. Frances is accredited for insertion of long acting contraception and to provide antenatal shared care for Royal Prince Alfred Hospital and Canterbury Hospital. Outside of medicine, Frances enjoys road trips, camping and exploring the great outdoors.

doctors.does_not_accept_new_patients_message_htm: Dr Greta Devane does not take on new patients.
doctors.statement: Greta is a final term registrar working towards her fellowship with the Royal Australian College of General Practitioners. She has just returned to Sydney from Darwin where she spent six months working in Emergency Medicine, completing her Emergency Medicine Certificate and developing an interest in Aboriginal health. Prior to this Greta has worked in GP practices in rural NSW and Sydney, as well as working in a number of Sydney hospitals. Greta completed her medical degree at the University of Sydney in 2015 and also has a Bachelor of Science from the University of Queensland. Greta enjoys the variety that comes with general practice and her interests include women's health, mental health and the management of chronic health conditions. Outside of medicine, Greta enjoys swimming, exploring the outdoors and trying out new restaurants.

reasons.name: Brief Consult (5-15 minutes)
reasons.message:
If you are booking for a complex condition or more than one matter please book a >20 minute Standard or >40 minute Long consult. 
Brief consults are $89 ($50.25 out of pocket) for existing patients and $146 ($70.95 out of pocket) for new patients. Medicare rebates are provided on the spot with a valid debit card. Please be aware, as of 01/01/2021 all children above the age of 5 are billed at a discounted rate. Please be aware that our fees are higher on weekends, please check our website or call reception to confirm the price.

clinic.name: Montrose Medical Practice
clinic.blurb:
Montrose Medical Practice is a private billing family practice located in the heart of Glebe. Founded in 2009, Montrose has been lovingly restored and renovated to create a welcoming environment for our patients while also showcasing the rich cultural heritage of the building, which has been used as a surgery and doctors’ residence since 1899. 
 
Our vision at Montrose is to provide you and your family with quality healthcare in a warm and caring environment with an emphasis on preventative health. We have a great team of dedicated general practitioners, nurses and allied health professionals, including a clinical psychologist and podiatrist.  Pathology is also provided onsite through Douglas Hanly Moir. They are open Monday – Friday 9am-1pm.

clinic.billing_policy: Montrose Medical Practice is a private billing practice. Our practice is equipped with Medicare Easyclaim which gives you the choice of having your Medicare claiming done on the spot with Medicare rebate deposited into your bank account using an EFTPOS card. Discounted fee applies to pension card holders, health care cardholders, full-time students and children from the age of 5. Children under the age of 5 who hold a valid Medicare card are bulk billed except on the weekend. Bulk billing appointments will be offered for children age 5- 15, during the week with Dr Manny until the 30th of June 2021
clinic.transport_info: Metered parking is available on Glebe Point Road or 2 hour free parking is available in Broadway shopping center.
